text: is a Japanese football player. She played for the Japan national team. ==Biography== Muramatsu was born in Setagaya, Tokyo on October 23, 1994. She was promoted to Nippon TV Beleza (later Nippon TV Tokyo Verdy Beleza) from the youth team in 2011. She was selected Best Eleven in 2015 and 2016. In 2010, Muramatsu was selected the Japan U-17 national team for 2010 U-17 World Cup. She played 5 games and Japan won the 2nd place. In August 2015, she was selected the Japan national team for 2015 East Asian Cup. At this competition, on August 4, she debuted against South Korea.
